{
  "uuid": "3474bf7ce6e36e11f33d7b1f46f8a22c",
  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Pet Transport",
  "description": "<p><strong>Company Overview / Employee Value Proposition</strong></p><p>PAWSITIVE IMAGE LLP, a new grooming destination to pamper your pets. We believe in creating a positive image for lovable pals. Pet grooming with love, one dog at a time.</p><p><strong>Job Summary</strong></p><p>You will be responsible for safely transporting pets, maintaining the vehicle, and assisting with pet handling to support smooth operations and customer satisfaction.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Drive pets safely to and from designated locations according to schedule</li><li>The working days from Tuesday to Sunday (6 days).</li><li>The transportation pick up in the morning between 7 am to 830 am. </li><li>The transportation returning time in the afternoon will be between 2.30 pm to 4.30 pm.</li><li>Handle pets carefully during transportation to ensure their comfort and safety</li><li>Maintain cleanliness of the vehicle by washing and cleaning regularly</li><li>Carry and lift pet cages safely to prevent injury to pets and yourself</li><li>Communicate clearly with pet owners to confirm pick-up and drop-off locations</li></ul><p><strong>Required competencies and certifications</strong></p><ul><li>Hold a valid Class 3 driving license</li><li>Have at least 2 years of driving experience</li></ul><p><strong>Preferred competencies and qualifications</strong></p><ul><li>Demonstrate care and attentiveness in handling pets during transportation</li></ul>",
